NASA‚Äôs Orion Spacecraft Completes Milestone for Artemis III Crew Module

The pressure vessel is the primary structure for Orion‚Äôs crew module, joined together using state-of-the-art welding by technicians from lead contractor Lockheed Martin.

Both the Orion spacecraft and the Space Launch System (SLS) rocket are making progress towards Artemis missions to the Moon. Artemis II will follow as the first crewed mission, taking humans around the Moon and back to Earth to pave the way for future missions to the Gateway and the lunar surface aboard a commercial human landing system.
